==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lactodensimeter
<hw>Lac`to*den*sim"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lac</ets>, <ets>lactis</ets>, milk + E.
<ets>densimeter</ets>.]</ety> <def>A form of hydrometer, specially
graduated, for finding the density of milk, and thus discovering whether
it has been mixed with water or some of the cream has been
removed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lactometer</ent>⟦br⟧
